Implement Phase 37: Realtime Gateway Stabilization + Test Runtime Isolation.

Context:
Phase 36 added server command center scripts and secret-safe Git workflow.
Before Phase 37, make validate-fast must pass.

Goal:
Stabilize zDash realtime WebSocket behavior across local dev, test runtime, and production reverse proxy, while ensuring tests never accidentally depend on a running local backend.

Hard safety requirements:
- Do not enable live trading.
- Keep DRY_RUN=true by default.
- Keep LIVE_TRADING_ACK=false.
- Keep MT5_ENABLED=false.
- Keep PRODUCTION_ALLOW_LIVE_ACTIONS=false.
- Keep RISK_GUARDIAN_ENABLED=true.
- Do not add real broker execution.
- Do not weaken safety-scan or push protection.
- Do not commit real secrets.

Part 1: Realtime WebSocket routing audit

Audit frontend and backend websocket paths.

Current required behavior:
- Frontend realtime channels must connect through API-prefixed backend paths.
- Backend must support:
  /api/realtime/ws
  /api/realtime/ws/events
  /api/realtime/ws/risk
  /api/realtime/ws/scheduler
  /api/realtime/ws/content

Frontend channel mapping should be:
events    -> /api/realtime/ws/events
risk      -> /api/realtime/ws/risk
scheduler -> /api/realtime/ws/scheduler
content   -> /api/realtime/ws/content

Backend must reject unknown channels cleanly with close code 4003 and reason CHANNEL_NOT_ALLOWED.

Part 2: Realtime backend channel support

Update backend/app/api/realtime.py if needed.

Requirements:
- Keep existing /api/realtime/ws behavior.
- Add /api/realtime/ws/{channel}.
- Allowed channels:
  - events
  - risk
  - scheduler
  - content
- Use the same broadcaster, heartbeat, connection manager, entitlement checks, and quota checks.
- Do not duplicate websocket logic unnecessarily.
- Include channel in pong payload metadata.
- Preserve compatibility endpoint /api/realtime/ws/events.

Part 3: Frontend realtime client hardening

Update frontend/src/realtime/client.ts if needed.

Requirements:
- Use /api/realtime/ws/* paths.
- Respect VITE_REALTIME_ENABLED=false in tests.
- Keep test runtime default disabled.
- Do not force VITE_API_BASE_URL or VITE_WS_BASE_URL in frontend/.env.test.
- Add clear fallback behavior when WebSocket is disabled:
  connected=false
  connecting=false
  retryInMs=null

Part 4: Test runtime isolation

Ensure frontend tests do not depend on a live backend.

Create or update:
frontend/.env.test

It must contain only:

VITE_ENABLE_MOCK_FALLBACK=true
VITE_REALTIME_ENABLED=false

Do not set:
VITE_API_BASE_URL
VITE_WS_BASE_URL

Reason:
URL derivation tests expect default localhost:8005 and explicit https/wss conversion behavior.

Part 5: Content pipeline test stability

Fix ContentPipeline tests without weakening safety behavior.

Requirements:
- Tests should pass whether backend is stopped or running with empty content DB.
- Do not require real backend content items.
- Options:
  A) mock listContentItems in the test, or
  B) make ContentPipeline render an empty-state safety panel that still contains:
     - Policy notes
     - Dry-run publish
     - approval-gated messaging
- Preferred: mock API responses in ContentPipeline.test.tsx so tests are deterministic.
- Keep publish button disabled until approved.
- Do not enable real social posting.

Part 6: Add focused tests

Add or update tests:

frontend/src/tests/RealtimeClient.test.ts
- verifies events path is /api/realtime/ws/events
- verifies risk path is /api/realtime/ws/risk
- verifies scheduler path is /api/realtime/ws/scheduler
- verifies content path is /api/realtime/ws/content
- verifies VITE_REALTIME_ENABLED=false disables socket opening

frontend/src/tests/useCollaboration.test.ts
- must keep existing default URL expectations:
  ws://localhost:8005/api/collaboration/ws/collaboration/w1
  wss://zdash.zeaz.dev/api/collaboration/ws/collaboration/w1

frontend/src/tests/ContentPipeline.test.tsx
- deterministic mock content item
- expects Policy notes
- expects Dry-run publish
- expects button disabled until approved

Backend tests:
- add backend test for /api/realtime/ws/{channel} allowed channel logic if websocket test utilities exist.
- If websocket test utilities are not available, add pure unit coverage for channel validation helper.

Part 7: Makefile validation helper

Add target only if missing:

test-frontend-isolated:
- cd frontend
- run vitest with test env
- must not require running backend

Do not duplicate existing targets.

Part 8: Docs

Create:

docs/runbooks/REALTIME_GATEWAY.md

Include:
- realtime channel paths
- local dev websocket setup
- test isolation rules
- common 403 causes
- how to disable realtime locally:
  VITE_REALTIME_ENABLED=false
- how to restart server:
  make server-stop
  make server-start
  make server-status

Part 9: Validation

Run:

make server-stop || true
make validate-fast
make server-start
make server-status
make server-stop

Acceptance criteria:
- make validate-fast passes.
- frontend tests do not depend on running backend.
- no websocket 403 spam for valid realtime channels.
- unknown websocket channels are rejected cleanly.
- useCollaboration URL tests still pass.
- ContentPipeline tests pass with deterministic data.
- no duplicate Makefile targets.
- no secrets in tracked files.